        "contact": {
          "email": "contact@fishfish.gg"
        },
        "description": "FishFish is an automated service designed to quickly detect and mitigate phishing threats before they can be exploited for malicious purposes. It provides a streamlined solution for identifying harmful resources efficiently.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://api.fishfish.gg"
          }
        ],
        "termsOfService": "https://fishfish.gg/",
        "title": "Anti-Phishing Detection",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Check whether a domain or URL is known phishing, malware, or safe via the community-run FishFish threat database",
        "homepage": "https://fishfish.gg/",
        "docs_url": "https://api.fishfish.gg/docs",
        "license_short": "No licence published; usage gated by anti-abuse policy.",
        "license_md": "- No explicit licence is published alongside the FishFish API or its threat data.\n- Read access to domain and URL lookups is open; write operations require an API key as an anti-abuse measure.\n- Treat returned classifications as advisory and verify before taking automated action against users.",
        "about_md": "[FishFish](https://fishfish.gg/) is an anti-phishing service that focuses on quick, automated detection of malicious resources before they can be used at scale. The community maintains a shared database of domains and URLs categorised as `safe`, `phishing`, or `malware`, exposed through the API at `https://api.fishfish.gg`.\n\nWhat you can do with the API:\n\n- Look up a single domain via `GET /v1/domains/{domain}` to retrieve its current category.\n- List tracked domains via `GET /v1/domains` for bulk consumption.\n- Equivalent `/v1/urls` endpoints exist for full URL classifications.\n- Subscribe to live database changes over a WebSocket stream at `wss://api.fishfish.gg/v1/stream` instead of polling.\n\nRead endpoints are publicly accessible with CORS enabled. Submitting, editing, or deleting entries requires an API token in the `Authorization` header; session tokens issued via `/users/@me/tokens` are valid for one hour and must be refreshed from a long-lived main token.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "detection": "Phishing and malware classifications for domains and URLs, served from the FishFish threat database under `/v1/domains/{domain}` and `/v1/urls/{url}`, with a `wss://api.fishfish.gg/v1/stream` feed for live updates."
        },
